<tr><td nowrap width="20%" align="right" valign=baseline><b>Serial Number Database:</b></td><td colspan=4 align="left" valign=baseline><a href="redirect.pl?http://www.ipsnd.net/View.aspx?id=1887">View at <I>The Internet Pinball Serial Number Database</I> (IPSND.net)</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<font size="-1"><I>(External site)</i></font></td></tr><tr><td nowrap width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Theme: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline>Sports - Football</td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Notable Features: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline><a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Flipper">Flippers</a> (4), <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Pop_Bumper">Pop&nbsp;bumpers</a> (3) 7-bank <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Drop_Target">drop&nbsp;targets</a> (1), <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Standup_Target">Standup&nbsp;targets</a> (2), <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Spinning_Target">Spinning&nbsp;target</a> (1), Star <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Rollover">rollover</a> (1). Bounce-back <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Outlane">outlanes</a> allow the player to <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Nudge">nudge</a> a draining ball back into play.</td></tr>
<tr><td width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Design by: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline><span title="Click here to perform a search for all pinball games that 'Jim&nbsp;Patla' was connected with."><a href="search.pl?searchtype=advanced&amp;ppl=Jim%20Patla">Jim&nbsp;Patla</a></span></td></tr>
<tr><td width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Art by: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline><span title="Click here to perform a search for all pinball games that 'Paul&nbsp;Faris' was connected with."><a href="search.pl?searchtype=advanced&amp;ppl=Paul%20Faris">Paul&nbsp;Faris</a></span></td></tr>
<!-- 1365 == Kick-Off -->
<!-- 1677 == Night Rider -->
<!-- 793 == Evel Knievel -->
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Notes: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline>The 4-player version of this game is <span title="Click here to open a new window and display Bally's 1977 'Kick Off'"><a target="game1365" href="machine.cgi?id=1365">Bally's 1977 'Kick Off'</a></span>, with a different sports theme.<br><br>We previously had credited Dick White as artist for this game. Paul Faris provided us this information:<P style="padding-left:30px;"><I>When Bally hired me, they had me work on the game 'Quarterback' as my first assignment. I actually had to make a 4-player game with a soccer theme to be sold in Europe (because Europeans favored 4-player games). That one was called <a target="game1365" href="machine.cgi?id=1365">Kick-Off</a>. I know they prototyped it but I don't know if they ever produced it. I think Dick White did the first version of the Quarterback glass and management asked me to redo it along with the soccer version. I don't think I ever saw a production version of either game before I went on to <a target="game1677" href="machine.cgi?id=1677">Night Rider</a> and then <a target="game793" href="machine.cgi?id=793">Evel Knievel</a>. That is as much as I know.</i></P><P></td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" align=right valign=baseline><b>Photos in: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline>
<a href="redirect.pl?http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/0764320742/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&camp=1789&creative=390957&creativeASIN=0764320742&linkCode=as2&tag=theinternetpi-20&linkId=Z72T2JLDLWNKE4TA">The Pinball Compendium 1970-1981</a>, page 88<br>
Mike Pacak's Pinball Flyer Reference Book G-R<br>
</td></tr>
